    "body": "> I know most of that stuff will be used eventually, but given the ease of resurrecting it, I'd prefer to take the route of delete and then revive later when we need it again.\r\n\r\nI think we are better off finding a different way to indicate that the sharding code is dormant for the next phase:\r\n\r\nWe are setting ourselves up to do a lot of work when reviving the code, because the internal APIs are so fluid. I expect that it's going to be like the recent merge of the sharding branch, all over again. Instead, if we leave the code in, the tests will catch it when internal API changes break the dormant sharding code.",
